    "description": "Write a Python function called `sort_length_1` that must sort strings by length then alphabetically, variant 1. Practice sorting key.\nDifficulty: Easy.\nExamples:\n  sort_length_1([\"bbb\", \"a\", \"cc\"]) -> [\"a\", \"cc\", \"bbb\"]\n  sort_length_1([\"x\", \"aa\", \"b\"]) -> [\"b\", \"x\", \"aa\"]",
    "initialCode": "def sort_length_1(words):\n    pass",
    "solution": "# Example 1: canonical function approach\ndef sort_length_1(words):\n    return sorted(words, key=lambda word: (len(word), word))\n\nprint(sort_length_1([\"bbb\", \"a\", \"cc\"]))  # Expected: [\"a\", \"cc\", \"bbb\"]\n\n# Example 2: helper function approach\ndef solve_problem_4958(words):\n    def calculate():\n        return sorted(words, key=lambda word: (len(word), word))\n    return calculate()\n\nprint(solve_problem_4958([\"x\", \"aa\", \"b\"]))\n\n# Example 3: static method approach\nclass Problem4958Solution:\n    @staticmethod\n    def sort_length_1(words):\n        return sorted(words, key=lambda word: (len(word), word))\n\nprint(Problem4958Solution.sort_length_1([]))\n\n# Example 4: assigned result approach\nresult = sort_length_1([\"bbb\", \"a\", \"cc\"])\nprint(result)\n\n# Example 5: direct call\nprint(sort_length_1([\"x\", \"aa\", \"b\"]))",
